OSOGBO – Osun State Government has ordered manhunt for the killers of Fulani herdsmen that took place at Wasimi Village in Irewole Local Government Area of the state. It would be recalled that some gunmen stormed the village in the early hours of Sunday and started shooting sporadically killing no fewer than six herders and several others injured. It was gathered that the herdsmen and the local have been leaving peacefully with no crisis before the incident. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! Deputy Governor, Benedict Alabi, who visited the scene of the incident on Sunday condemned the killing describing it as sad and unfortunate. Alabi paid a condolence visit to the bereaved family saying it was a case of brutal assasination stressing that the perpetrators would be brought to book in no distant time. Gov. Uzodimma Decries Existence Of Ghost Workers On Imo’s Payroll Rabiu Donates N200m To Sokoto Varsity Alabi, who visited the scene on behalf of Governor Oyetola was received by scores of family members of the deceased and some leaders in the community disclosed that the state government has ordered the security agencies in the state to fish out the evildoers and bring them before the law. The Osun Deputy Governor was accompanied on the visit by the state Commissioner for Finance, Bola Oyebamiji and the Special Adviser to the Governor on Security, Mrs Abiodun Ige. He asked members of the community and the citizens of the state at large to remain calm, assuring that government would continue to provide adequate security across the state. In his words, “This is a very unfortunate incident and we are so sad about it as a government. It is shocking and strange to our communities.”